Section 1:
1 L.D. 1654
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1095, L.D. 1654, “An Act to Allow a
10 Grace Period for the Payment of Excise Tax for Adult Use Cannabis Cultivation Facilities”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §4921, sub-§9-A is enacted to read:
14 9-A. Products manufacturing facility. "Products manufacturing facility" has the
15 same meaning as in Title 28-B, section 102-A, subsection 51.
16 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §4923, sub-§6, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 231, Pt. B, §7 and
17 amended by PL 2021, c. 669, §5, is amended to read:
18 6. Multiple licenses. When a cultivation facility licensee also holds a license to
19 operate another cannabis establishment, the taxes imposed by subsections 1 to 4 apply to
20 any transfer of cannabis from the cultivation facility to the other cannabis establishment
21 licensee or, if no such transfer is made, to any activity undertaken pursuant to Title 28‑B,
22 section 501, subsection 2 or 4 with regard to cannabis cultivated by the cultivation facility.
23 Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §4923, sub-§7 is enacted to read:
24 7. Sales and transfers between licensed cultivation facilities. Notwithstanding
25 subsection 6, an excise tax is not imposed on a sale of adult use cannabis to a cultivation
26 facility or on a transfer of adult use cannabis to a cultivation facility. This subsection does
27 not apply to a sale or transfer by a nursery cultivation facility pursuant to Title 28-B, section
28 501, subsection 3, paragraph C.
29 Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §4923, sub-§8 is enacted to read:
30 8. Transfers to and from products manufacturing facility. Notwithstanding
31 subsection 6, an excise tax is not imposed on the transfer of adult use cannabis to a products
32 manufacturing facility when the adult use cannabis is returned to the original cultivation
33 facility in the same form and weight within 30 days.
Page 1 - 132LR1647(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1095, L.D. 1654
1 Sec. 5. 36 MRSA §4924, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 231, Pt. B, §7, is amended to
2 read:
3 §4924. Returns; payment of excise tax
4 On For returns filed for periods ending before January 1, 2026, on or before the 15th
5 day of each month, a cultivation facility licensee shall file a return, as required by the
6 assessor, and pay to the assessor all excise taxes due under this chapter for the preceding
7 calendar month.
8 For filing periods beginning on or after January 1, 2026, a cultivation facility licensee
9 shall file a return and pay to the assessor all excise taxes due under this chapter pursuant to
10 subsections 1 and 2.
11 1. Return due date. On or before the 15th day of each month, a cultivation facility
12 licensee shall file a return on a form as required by the assessor. The return must report all
13 adult use cannabis sold or transferred to other licensees during the preceding calendar
14 month.
15 2. Payment due date. Beginning June 2026, on or before the 15th day of each month,
16 a cultivation facility licensee shall remit the excise tax imposed on sales and transfers
17 required to be reported on a return filed pursuant to subsection 1 120 days after the filing
18 of that return.
19 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
20 allocations are made.
21 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
22 Revenue Services, Bureau of 0002
23 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for computer programming costs.
24 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
25 All Other $21,200 $0
26 __________ __________
27 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $21,200 $0
2284 '
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment exempts from the cannabis excise tax the sale or transfer of adult use
3333 cannabis to a cultivation facility and exempts the transfer of adult use cannabis to a products
3344 manufacturing facility when the adult use cannabis is returned within 30 days to the original
3355 cultivation facility in the same form and weight.
36 Beginning January 1, 2026, the amendment establishes new filing and tax payment
37 guidelines for cannabis excise tax. Excise tax filings and excise tax payments remain due
Page 2 - 132LR1647(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1095, L.D. 1654
318 on a monthly basis, but excise tax payments for any given month are for the excise tax
329 return filed 120 days prior to the payment.
430 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
441 (See attached)
Page 3 - 132LR1647(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
